🌐 Computer Networks
1️⃣ TCP vs UDP (Deep Understanding)

You already know basics → now let’s go deeper.

TCP Internals (Reliable System)

TCP ensures:

✔ Data arrives
✔ In correct order
✔ No duplication

How TCP Does This
Sequence numbers → order tracking
Acknowledgment → confirmation
Retransmission → resend lost data
Mental Model 📦

Courier service with:

tracking ID
delivery confirmation
resend if lost
UDP Internals (Fast System)

UDP:

sends data directly
no tracking
no guarantee
Mental Model 🚀

Throwing multiple balls → no checking if they reached.

Why Both Exist
Need	Protocol
Accuracy	TCP
Speed	UDP
Memory Trick 🧠

TCP = Safe but slow
UDP = Fast but risky

2️⃣ Sliding Window (Flow Control Mechanism)
Simple Idea

Controls how much data can be sent before receiving acknowledgment.

Mental Model (Water Pipe 🚰)
Pipe size = window size
Bigger pipe → more flow
Smaller pipe → less flow
How It Works

Sender sends multiple packets without waiting.

Receiver sends ACK → window slides forward.

Why It Works

Improves efficiency → avoids waiting for each packet.

Memory Trick

Window = How much data you can send at once

3️⃣ ARQ Protocols (Error Recovery)
Simple Idea

If data is lost → resend it.

Types
Stop-and-Wait
Go-Back-N
Selective Repeat
Mental Model

Teacher gives questions:

If wrong → redo
If missing → resend
Example

Stop-and-Wait:

Send → wait → send next

Go-Back-N:

If error → resend multiple

Selective Repeat:

Only resend missing ones
Why It Works

Ensures reliable communication.

Memory Trick

ARQ = Automatic Repeat Request

